<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1562,1947]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,224,1562,1587]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Color.</emphasis>
Vertex, pronotum, mesonotum and scutellum with red longitudinal bands. Costal margin of forewing with subapical reflexed dark veinlets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1562,1947]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1634,1659]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Body.</emphasis>
Head strongly produced, triangular or spatulate, lateral margins foliaceous. Face with longitudinal keel at front. Ocellus 2â€“ 
<date box="[367,394,1671,1695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">3x</date>
of their own diameter from eye, lying below anterior margin of head, not visible from above. Frontoclypeus not tumid, clypeal sulcus prominent. Pronotum with a variable medial carinae. Forewing with two closed anteapical cells, with recurved veins in corium from outer anteapical cell. Protibia dorsal macrosetae 1+3. Metafemur apex macrosetae 2+1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1562,1947]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1814,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Male.</emphasis>
Pygofer side without macrosetae, with short tooth on apical half near ventral margin. Valve long, triangular. Subgenital plate triangular or squarish, macrosetae uniseriate. Connective Y-shaped. Aedeagus with triangular base, shaft bent at base, nearly parallel to aedeagal base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
